1
00:00:03,808 --> 00:00:08,587
Shankaracharya, he is such 
a brahmachari-sannyasi,

2
00:00:08,587 --> 00:00:13,366
he has no idea about 
the male-female relationship.

3
00:00:13,366 --> 00:00:15,913
But he can understand, 
it's in Vedic literature,

4
00:00:15,913 --> 00:00:18,600
hint to that, indicated.

5
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:22,883
He must understand what is madhura-rasa, 
but he doesn't get it.

6
00:00:22,883 --> 00:00:26,806
By personal experience 
he can't project what that means.

7
00:00:26,806 --> 00:00:30,600
[Life Passing By | Smash the Illusion]

8
00:00:30,710 --> 00:00:37,299
So one king is dying nearby, 
and he enters the body of that king,

9
00:00:37,399 --> 00:00:41,398
so through his queens 
he can understand what this is.

10
00:00:41,398 --> 00:00:47,578
But he also heard, the power—
this is the greatest illusion of Krishna

11
00:00:47,683 --> 00:00:51,123
as told in Bhagavatam 
and other places.

12
00:00:52,180 --> 00:00:58,114
So he tells them [his disciples], 
“In the event that I can't come out of it,

13
00:00:58,204 --> 00:01:02,888
this Moha Mud[gara stotram] ...
I wrote this stotram.

14
00:01:02,888 --> 00:01:08,244
You kneel ... (because his body is lying), 
you kneel down next to my body

15
00:01:08,244 --> 00:01:12,622
('cause he is like in a trance and 
his soul is entering another body, etc.)

16
00:01:12,622 --> 00:01:17,430
and you start chanting 
these slokas in my ear,

17
00:01:17,430 --> 00:01:22,366
and that will smash the illusion 
and save me.”

18
00:01:22,366 --> 00:01:24,272
And that's what they do.

19
00:01:24,272 --> 00:01:31,148
And Gurudev liked those slokas, 
especially this dina-yāminyau sloka

20
00:01:31,148 --> 00:01:33,634
that was on his veranda in Kolkata.

21
00:01:33,634 --> 00:01:36,642
And he would look at it all the time 
and quote it.

22
00:01:36,642 --> 00:01:44,126
It's about life passing by, 
wasting time.

23
00:01:44,126 --> 00:01:49,214
And Gurudev liked to tell us 
a story of Lal Babu,

24
00:01:49,214 --> 00:01:53,802
the millionaire, 
who is marketing one day.

25
00:01:53,802 --> 00:01:58,228
And it is towards the end of the day, 
and he is getting very picky

26
00:01:58,228 --> 00:02:01,584
about his mangoes or fruits, 
whatever it's he's selecting.

27
00:02:01,584 --> 00:02:08,112
And the shopkeeper says, "Lal Babu, 
it's late, look, sun's going down.

28
00:02:08,112 --> 00:02:12,000
Sun is setting, it's getting late, 
I wanna go home.

29
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:17,026
It's the end of the day, hurry up, 
make your mind up, choose."

30
00:02:17,026 --> 00:02:18,726
That's what he is saying.

31
00:02:18,726 --> 00:02:20,206
But then, Gurudev said,

32
00:02:20,206 --> 00:02:23,998
like a thunderbolt 
it hits the heart of Lal Babu...

33
00:02:23,998 --> 00:02:27,870
What we call vartma-pradarśak, 
patha-pradarśak guru,

34
00:02:27,870 --> 00:02:31,642
some divine current flowing through them, 
and he is thinking,

35
00:02:31,642 --> 00:02:34,954
“It's guru, it's Krishna telling me,

36
00:02:34,954 --> 00:02:39,086
‘The sun's going down, 
your time is running out.

37
00:02:39,086 --> 00:02:45,849
You're wasting your time thinking about 
all these choices that lie before you.

38
00:02:45,849 --> 00:02:50,740
When you don't realize death 
is coming knocking at your door soon.

39
00:02:50,740 --> 00:02:52,751
So make your choice now’”.

40
00:02:52,751 --> 00:02:59,033
And he gets the inspiration to give up 
the world and dedicate himself exclusively.

41
00:02:59,033 --> 00:03:00,885
It's a sloka like that.

42
00:03:00,885 --> 00:03:06,177
And Gurudev liked that, and it was right 
in front of him, that's where he put it.

